<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/lordswms/2005-04-05a.80.3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100013" speakername="Baroness Amos" colon=":" colnum="80"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds05/text/50405-47.htm#50405-47_spnew0">
	<p pid="a.80.3/1">My right honourable friend the Minister of State for Northern Ireland has made the following Ministerial Statement.</p>
	<p pid="a.80.3/2">I am pleased to announce that the Northern Ireland Discretionary Social Fund budget for 2005&ndash;06 will be &pound;59.59 million. Some &pound;13.32 million will be allocated to grants; &pound;46.17 million to loans and &pound;0.1 million will be held as a contingency reserve. The new allocations represent an increase of &pound;1.34 million over the initial gross budget set at April 2004. This increase will be funded through higher loan recoveries, plus an increase in net Treasury funding of &pound;0.68 million for this year. This &pound;0.68 million is the third and final instalment of the increases to the discretionary social fund announced in the autumn 2002 Pre-Budget Report.</p>
	<p pid="a.80.3/3">The community care grant budget has been increased by &pound;0.68 million to &pound;13.32 million. This will provide more help to customers, in particular families with children and the disabled.</p>
	<p pid="a.80.3/4">The loans budget has been increased to &pound;46.17 million, an increase of &pound;0.66 million on the initial 2004&ndash;05 loans budget. To improve the fairness of the scheme, budgets will be allocated in a way that will over time achieve greater consistency of outcome for customers wherever they live.</p>
	<p pid="a.80.3/5"><a href="/pa/ld200405/ldlwa/050405ws1.pdf">/pa/ld200405/ldlwa/050405ws1.pdf</a>, together with a note explaining the basis on which they have been made, have been placed in the House of Commons Library.</p>
</speech>
